  "conformsToProfile": "https://uofa.net/vocab#ProfileMinimal",
  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Submission requirements are described in internal document REQ-NAGARAJA-001, which mandates that all three quantities of interest (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) be predicted within 10% of experimental mean and that the normalised validation metric E/uval remain below 1.96. This Minimal-profile package captures the credibility evidence; the formal requirement object is defined at https://uofa.net/nagaraja/req/req-001 but the top-level bindsRequirement link is intentionally absent per the Minimal profile declaration.",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/claim/claim-fea-f1717-noncannulated",
