    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment accepted. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs required 3) is accepted with documented justification: the COU is restricted to quasi-static loading at the single ASTM F1717 prescribed rate, and sensitivity to load rate is not clinically relevant for the static compression-bending submission context. All three QoIs pass the quantitative validation metric (E/uval < 1.96). Model risk level 3 credibility requirements are satisfied in aggregate. Package conforms to ProfileMinimal; full requirement traceability is maintained in internal document REQ-NAGARAJA-001.",
